kjerken wrote:
&gt; There are two features I would like to see in Heritrix, and before I
&gt; implement them, I would like to ask if anyone else has, and if so, if
&gt; they would be willing to share them.
&gt;
&gt; The first is to insert the results of a crawl into a database (MySQL,
&gt; as usual).  I know at least two other people have gone over this
&gt; before on the list, but has their code ever been suggested for
&gt; incorporation or made public?  (I&#39;ve e-mailed them, but thought I&#39;d
&gt; ask here just in case).
We&#39;ve not see hide nor hair round these parts.
&gt;
&gt; The second is a programmatic interface to the WorkQueue;  I would like
&gt; to start a crawl with an empty queue, and as a result of processing
&gt; elsewhere, in another program, insert seeds into the queue remotely.
&gt; Has anyone
&gt; written anything for this?
Have you considered using JMX to do this?  The API allows remote 
submission of seeds.  See 
http://crawler.archive.org/articles/user_manual.html#mon_com for more on 
remote control of Heritrix. Also of note, its possible to set the 
crawler to pause on start and have it wait on submission of seeds, etc.  
Same can be done for end-of-crawl: rather than die after all URLs have 
been exhausted, the crawler can be set to go into a holding pattern.

